# Keep the container build context small.
#
# The only image (claude/docker/Dockerfile) builds the `basecamp` Python tool,
# which needs src/, claude/, pyproject.toml, and uv.lock — nothing else. The
# rest of the repo (the retired Pi package checkouts, virtualenvs, node_modules,
# git history) would otherwise be tarred up and sent to the engine on every
# build, so it is excluded here.

# Virtualenvs, dependencies, VCS, caches
.venv/
node_modules/
.git/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.playwright-mcp/
**/__pycache__/

# Retired Pi extension trees (large vendored checkouts, unused by the image)
core/
workspace/
pi/
pi-ui/
pi-git/
pi-tasks/
pi-swarm/
pi-browser/
pi-companion/
pi-engineering/
pi-bash-reviewer/

# Docs / tests / misc not needed to build the basecamp tool
docs/
tests/
migrations/
scripts/
